To solve this problem, we first find out the total number of batarangs and then subtract the number found on Batman. Since 20 are in his utility belt, 30 are in his cape, and the rest (100 - 50 =) 50 are in his Batmobile:

```
\boxed{
\begin{aligned}
& \text{{Batarangs in Batmobile}} = \\
& \hspace{12mm}\text{{Total Batarangs}} - \text{{Batarangs on Utility Belt}} - \text{{Batarangs in Cape}}\\
&= 100 - (20 + 30)\\
&= 50
\end{aligned}
}
```

The boxed equation above solves the problem of finding out the number of batarangs in Batman's Batmobile.

